From c2ecc0558492b2e690bceb2b3a6b2ddc83593457 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Zach Taylor <zctaylor.work@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 11:05:27 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 01/48] Add tmux-style leader-key (ctrl-b) chords for tab
 management

Introduces a configurable leader/prefix key (default ctrl-b) so you can run
actions with tmux-style chords, e.g. 'ctrl-b ,' renames the active tab.

The chord engine is upstream (Matcher::push_keystroke already matches
multi-keystroke sequences and the input pipeline only forwards to the PTY on
MatchResult::None). This adds:
- app/src/util/leader.rs: LEADER constant + an extensible (suffix -> WorkspaceAction)
  table, registered on the Workspace context (ancestor of the focused terminal).
  Defaults: , rename tab | c new tab | & close tab | n/p next/prev tab.
- workspace::init: calls register_leader_bindings(app).
- util::mod: declares the leader module.
- bindings.rs: allowlists ctrl-b in PTY_NON_COMPLIANT_KEYSTROKES so the leader is
  captured from the shell (tmux-style) and passes binding validation.

Not yet compiled locally (repo pins Rust 1.92.0 via nix devshell); verify with
'nix develop && cargo check -p warp'.
